HEADWORD: Caryatides
<hw>Car`y*at"i*des</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.,
fr. Gr. <?/ (<?/) priestesses in the temple of Diana (the Greek Artemis)
at Cary⟦ae⟧ (Gr. <?/), a village in Laconia; as an architectural term,
caryatids.]</ety> <fld>(Arch)</fld> <def>Caryatids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Corresponding male figures were called
